  "texts": [
    "Similarly, there are corpora designed for Named-Entity Recognition (NER) and Parts-Of-Speech (POS) tagging tasks.",
    "Genre-specific corpora have also been compiled for formal text from academic articles, journals, and conferences; informal text from emails, blogs, and webpages; spoken language from language databases; etc.",
    "This brings to light how resource-rich some of the nontechnical areas are, and how NLP models can be trained to achieve high levels of accuracy in their tasks.",
    "The term 'Technical text' is not a clearly defined one and has been used to described text data from various fields (Copeck et al., 1997).",
    "In the engineering and scientific community, the term 'technical' can take a few different meanings."
  ],
